   BLACKS-AIDS (Washington) _ Seventeen years after AIDS was first
recognized among gay white men in New York and San Francisco, the
disease in this country is becoming largely an epidemic among black
people, quietly devastating families and neighborhoods, yet all but
ignored by leading black institutions. By Sheryl Gay Stolberg.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
