<HEADLINE>
KNEE CYST KNOCKS STANKIEWICZ TO DL  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DON KETCHUM  
 AND BOB COHN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - While right-hander  &UR; Aaron Small joined the club
Saturday after being picked up on waivers from the Oakland
Athletics, veteran infielder
 &UR; Andy Stankiewicz was placed on the 15-day disabled list,
retroactive to Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Stankiewicz had arthroscopic surgery on his right knee during
spring training, and a magnetic resonance imaging taken recently
revealed that a cyst has grown on the inside of the area where the
surgery was performed.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; David Zeman, the team's orthopedic surgeon, was due to give
Stankiewicz an injection to help break up the cyst.
</P>
<P>
   ``When we were in Cincinnati recently, I noticed Andy didn't
quite have the quick first step he usually has, and he admitted the
knee had been bothering him,'' Manager  &UR; Buck Showalter said.
</P>
<P>
   Stankiewicz is hitting .196 with no homers and seven RBIs, and
he has played sparingly of late at second base.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's frustrating,'' Stankiewicz said. ``I was hoping I could
play through it, but it just didn't get any better. Hopefully, the
injection will take care of it and I can get back after the
All-Star break.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
Devo takes a breather &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Center fielder  &UR; Devon White, who had started all but four of the
Diamondbacks games, was given the day off Sunday to rest his sore
legs.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had been wanting to give him some time for the last three
games, and today seemed like a good day because we also have
another day Monday (today's exhibition game in South Bend, Ind.),''
Showalter said. &QL; 
 &QL; 
On to South Bend &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The team's game against the Class A South Bend affiliate will
begin at 4 p.m. today, Arizona time, at Koveleski Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're proud and excited to go,'' Showalter said. ``It's a
quality minor league facility, and it means a lot to the fans and
that community.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jorge Fabregas, on the disabled list because of a sore right
ankle, will catch for Arizona tonight, then a determination will be
made as to whether to activate him for the big club. Fabregas
caught most of the game for Triple-A Tucson on Saturday night. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Sellout string &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Sunday's crowd of 47,968 was the 16th sellout at Bank One
Ballpark and marked the third series sellout of the season. The
other two were against the Los Angeles Dodgers and the St. Louis
Cardinals.
</P>
<P>
   The season attendance total to date is 1,684,332 for 37 dates,
putting the team on a pace for 3.6 million to 3.8 million for the
season. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Average plunges to .650 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Going into the game, Seattle's  &UR; Edgar Martinez was 13 for 17
with three homers during his career against  &UR; Brian Anderson. Before
the series started Friday, Showalter told Anderson, ``I've seen a
lot of match-ups, but I've never seen a hitter own somebody like he
owns you.''
</P>
<P>
   Maybe Martinez is just renting now. He went went 0 for 3 against
Anderson before hitting a single off  &UR; Alan Embree in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's just a tough hitter,'' Anderson said. ``I feel my stuff's
improved since the last time I faced him. I figure, just attack
him. Don't avoid him.'' &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
