   AIDS-MAIN GENEVA _ Thousands of unborn babies in the Third World
soon will have a better chance at dodging AIDS, because of a new
program that will slash the price of an anti-HIV drug and
distribute the drug to HIV-positive pregnant women.The Joint United
Nations Program on HIV/AIDS (UNAIDS) and the World Health
Organization announced Monday at the 12th World AIDS Conference its
plan to launch pilot drug therapy programs in several developing
countries where mother-to-child HIV transmission is a serious
problem. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 7 p.m.
