lowest unemployment rate in a generation, more teens may have a
better pick of the jobs they want and it already looks as if more
teens are working. But there's more to a summer job than just
money, and several experts say teens can walk away from a summer
job with valuable experience in addition to cash. (Tanamachi,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   DOGS30 _ ATLANTA _ It's midmorning on a shaded nature trai. Tiny
women in skin-tight togs lurch and stumble, jerked along at full
gallop by huge, hard-charging dogs on long pastel leashes. Tall men
slow to a trot to keep from outpacing panting, sad-eyed miniature
schnauzers. Such places can be great laboratories to examine the
love people have for their pets _ and also man's inhumanity to dog,
says Stanley Coren, a psychologist and canine authority whose
avowed mission is to slash the human-dog divorce rate. He hopes to
do that by helping people make better choices when selecting a pet.
(Hendrick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
