<P>
   Computer graphics expert Michael Bailey dares scientists to
touch their subjects. Bailey's mix of science and sculpture enables
even microbiologists to forego viewing their subjects on computer
screens and to actually hold them in their hands. Kathy A. Svitil,
an associate editor at Discover magazine, reports.
