<P>
   &UR; A TOUCH OF SCIENCE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FIVE COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE OF CHARGE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,300 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KATHY A SVITIL &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Computer graphics expert Michael Bailey dares scientists to
touch their subjects. Bailey's mix of science and sculpture enables
even microbiologists to forego viewing their subjects on computer
screens and to actually hold them in their hands. Kathy A. Svitil,
an associate editor at Discover magazine, reports.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-TOUCH-IT!-SCIENCE-NYTSF. Sent to category codes
``l'' lifestyle news and ``a'' general news.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A SICKLE IN THE CLOUDS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ONE COLOR SLIDE IS AVAILABLE FREE OF CHARGE &QL; 
 &UR; (600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By CARL ZIMMER &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   A 70-million-year-old fossil bird recently found in Madagascar
may just clinch the argument that birds descended from two-legged
dinosaurs, reports Carl Zimmer, a senior editor at Discover
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   (slugged: BC-ANCIENT-BIRD-NYTSF. Sent to category codes ``l''
lifestyle news and ``a'' general news.)
