<HEADLINE>
PUBLIC STOCK TAX RULE TO EXPIRE 
</HEADLINE>
   By AMY DOAN  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
Starting tomorrow, a tax provision that lets you deduct the fair
market value of public stock given to private foundations will
expire. You'll only be allowed to deduct the ``cost basis'' _ or
purchase price _ of the stock gift. For more information on this
change and donations that qualify for fair market value deductions,
see the Peninsula Community Foundation Web site at www.pcf.org.
<TEXT>
<P>
   401(k) REPORTS: Fidelity Investments is improving its 401(k)
account holders' reports by providing an accumulated rate of return
for all of the customer's funds in the portfolio. This service
would be in addition to the usual individual fund performance
information. The new statements also will provide customers with
asset-allocation pie charts and tell them how their investments
have performed against such benchmark indices as the S&AMP;P 500 index.
</P>
<P>
   SPARE CHANGE: Want to know what people do with their spare
change? Coinstar posed that question recently in a national poll
and found out that close to three-quarters of us hoard our spare
coins instead of using them in daily transactions. In fact, the
most popular way to store those nickels and dimes is in a glass jar
(28 percent of respondents) compared with 13 percent who opt for an
old-fashioned piggy bank. For other poll results, go to
</P>
<P>
   www.coinstar.com.
</P>
<P>
   RETIREMENT SITE: Union Bank of California has launched a Web
site for its retirement plan participants, at
www.selectbenefit.com. The site provides in-depth information on
500 of its retirement plans. Participants can view their balances
and get loan and vesting information.
</P>
<P>
   Chronicle staff writer Amy Doan can be reached at
doana &LR; sfgate.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
