plans to move for Saturday, June 27, on the New York Times wire.
For questions, please call Marcus Chan at 415-777-8443.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; AURORA  &LR; _ Wall Street had a tepid reaction to yesterday's initial
public offering of Aurora Foods Inc., the San Francisco maker of
such well-known supermarket products as Duncan Hines cake mixes and
Aunt Jemima frozen waffles.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of the highly leveraged company ended the day at $21,
exactly the price at which they began trading. They peaked at a
lackluster $21.13 earlier in the day. By Carol Emert
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DIGITAL  &LR; _ Tom Abate's high-tech column.
