<P>
   SCIENCE-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Your science questions answered.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE-WATCH (Undated) _ News and notes on science.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HEALTH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OPTIMISM-HEALTH (Undated) _ Optimistic people are healthier, a
series of studies show. Among the studies are ones that link
thoughts and feelings to the health of the immune system and the
likelihood of getting colds. By Susan Gilbert.
</P>
<P>
   BRODY-HEALTH (Undated) _ The Personal Health column: In a
radical shift from the nutritional advice offered in previous
editions, the new edition of ``Baby and Child Care,'' Dr. Benjamin
Spock advises parents to provide an all-plant diet for their
children after the age of 2. But that is not necessarily what
American children and their already overworked parents could or
would readily adopt. By Jane E. Brody. (``l'' code)
</P>
