<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sun., July 5)  
 (JT)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CRUISES ON THE YANGTZE _ Regal China Cruises is offering a 30
percent saving on all summer cruises on the Yangtze River. The
discount is good for cruises that are booked by Aug. 1; travel must
be completed by Aug. 31. With the discounts, fares start at $581 a
person, double occupancy, for a five-night cruise. Three-day
cruises are also available, and there are further discounts for
children. All the itineraries take travelers to the site of the
Three Gorges hydroelectric dam project. The three German-built
ships accommodate from 258 to 270 passengers. Information: (800)
808-3388 or (212) 768-3388.
</P>
<P>
   CYCLING FOR LESS _ VBT has reduced prices by $100 on some fall
departures for three cycling vacations _ in Kentucky, California
and a combined Martha's Vineyard and Nantucket itinerary. With the
discounts, the six-night Kentucky Bluegrass Country trip
(highlights: Keeneland Race Course, Kentucky Horse Park and the
Shaker Village of Pleasant Hill), departing Oct. 10 and Oct. 17,
starts at $1,095; the five-night California Wine Country tour in
the Napa and Sonoma valleys leaving Oct. 25, Nov. 1 and Nov. 8
starts at $1,195, and the five-night Martha's Vineyard-Nantucket
trip departing Oct. 18 and Oct. 25 starts at $1,295. Prices include
lodging, breakfast daily, most dinners, guide, directions and van
support. Bicycle rentals are available for an extra charge. VBT is
a division of Grand Circle Travel. Information: (800) 245-3868.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH AMERICAN SALE _ A four-night Buenos Aires package,
including round-trip air fare and hotel accommodation, is offered
by Zeus Tours of New York. For departures from Wednesday to Dec. 3,
the price starts at $1,025 with accommodation at the Lafayette
Hotel; for departures Dec. 4 to 9, the price starts at $799. The
flights are Aerolineas Argentinas nonstops from Kennedy
International Airport. The package also includes daily breakfast, a
city orientation tour, transfers and hotel service charges and tax.
Optional tours and hotel upgrades are available. For reservations,
call (212) 221-0006 or (800) 447-5667.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK FOR $125 _ Discounts on New York hotel rooms are not
easy to come by these days, but the 561-room Millenium Hilton is
offering rooms on Friday or Saturday nights through Sept. 5 for
$125 a night. The hotel, at 55 Church St. in the financial
district, has an indoor swimming pool. Tax (13\ percent plus $2 a
room) is extra. Reservations: (212) 693-2001.
</P>
<P>
   The 300-room Crowne Plaza at the United Nations, on 42d Street
between First and Second Avenues, has Summertime Fun Rates through
Sept. 13, with prices ranging from $189 to $219 nightly, in single
or double occupancy; 14 days' advance reservation is required. Tax
is extra. The Crowne Plaza at the United Nations is the former
Tudor Hotel. Reservations: (800) 879-8836.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
