   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   NAACP-HOTEL _ WASHINGTON _ Conceding he aims to ``initimidate''
hotel chains into ``doing the right thing,'' NAACP President Kweisi
Mfume released the civil rights organization's second annual
lodging industry ratings on Monday. The Texas-based Omni hotel
chain was at the bottom of the list and Mfume said the NAACP had
purposfully excluded the Atlanta Omni in booking rooms and events
for its annual convention next month. (Dart, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA-FIRES _ Vice President Al Gore headed to fire-scorched
Florida with the promise of more federal aid and attention, but the
vice president can't bring what residents here need most _ rain.
Scattered thunderstorms were predicted for this afternoon, but
officials said it wouldn't be enough to douse flames and ease the
threat of more fires. (Williams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA:
8 p.m.
</P>
