<P>
   SALMON-AGREEMENT (Undated) A salmon conservation agreement
announced Friday is ``inequitable'' and will be ``devastating for
British Columbia fishermen,'' British Columbia Premier Glen Clark
said Monday. Clark was cut out of the agreement, which was
negotiated between Canada's federal fisheries ministry and
Washington Gov. Gary Locke. ``Canada is not ready to stand up to
the United States on this issue, so they cobble together a stop-gap
deal, and claim victory for what is really a defeat,'' Clark said
in an interview. The premier hinted that British Columbia will
again try legal action in American courts, and may ``reconsider''
costly salmon conservation measures if they only produce fish for
Americans to catch. Clark's charges were dismissed by Fisheries
Minister David Anderson, who argued that Canada and Washington have
taken long overdue, urgently needed measures to save imperiled
salmon stocks on both sides of the border. ``We don't want to get
mixed up in this,'' said Locke's fisheries adviser Curt Smitch.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   PHYSIO-MERGE (Seattle) Seattle-based Physio Control has merged
with Medtronic Inc. of Minneapolis. The Seattle company developed
and manufactures external defibrillators; the Minneapolis company
makes implantable defibrillators.
</P>
