<SLUG> BC-SOUNDSHOPPING30-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Kansas on the leading edge of the rock/classical fusion movement
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   After a 15-year absence, original vocalist-violinist Robby
Steinhardt has rejoined Kansas, which spotlights its new symphonic
album ``Always Never the Same'' with the Atlanta Stmphony Orchestra
on Wednesday in Atlanta. The River North release, recorded with the
London Symphony Orchestra, includes ``Dust in the Wind,'' other
Kansas hits, the Beatles' ``Eleanor Rigby'' and three new tunes.
</P>
<P>
   -- Billy Bragg &AMP; Wilco, ``Mermaid Avenue'' (Elektra). Brit
protest singer uses previously unrecorded Woody Guthrie lyrics.
</P>
<P>
   -- Def Squad, ``El Nino'' (Def Jam). Erick Sermon, Redman, Keith
Murray (huff and puff). Review in Thursday Living. Grade: C+.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Hav Plenty'' soundtrack (Yab Yum/Sony). Grade: B+.
</P>
<P>
   -- La Bouche, ``SOS'' (RCA). Dance darlings groove. Review in
Thursday Living. Grade: B-.
</P>
<P>
   -- Maxwell, ``Embrya'' (Columbia). Review in Thursday Living.
Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Mulan'' soundtrack (Disney). Nice visuals, but. ... Review
in Thursday Living. Grade: C-.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
