<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Global Motorsport Group Inc., Morgan Hill, Calif., a supplier of
custom replacement parts for Harley-Davidson and other motorcycles,
said Fremont Partners LP had lowered its offer for a 94 percent
stake in company, to $21.75 a share in cash from $23.
</P>
<P>
   Perrigo Co., Allegan, Mich., the maker of over-the-counter drug
and personal care products, said it would restructure its
operations. The planned actions include closing its Missouri and
California manufacturing plants and selling its personal care unit.
</P>
<P>
   Unit Instrument Inc., Yorba Linda, Calif., said it was in talks
to be bought by another company, whose name was not disclosed. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
