<HEADLINE>
ADVERTISING NOTES 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   US WEST SELECTS DDB NEEDHAM
</P>
<P>
   US West Inc. in Denver named the Chicago office of DDB Needham
Worldwide to handle its account Monday, with billings estimated at
$70 million to $80 million. The account had been handled for almost
two years by N.W. Ayer &AMP; Partners in New York, part of MacManus
Group, which declined to take part in a review.
</P>
<P>
   The review included DDB Needham Chicago, part of Omnicom Group,
and three other finalists: Bozell Worldwide in Seattle, part of
True North Communications; Campbell Mithun Esty in Minneapolis,
which is majority owned by the Interpublic Group of Companies, and
Martin/Williams in Minneapolis, also part of Omnicom.
</P>
<P>
   __
</P>
<P>
   PEOPLE
</P>
<P>
   _ Max Lefeld was named to the new position of creative director
at Siboney USA, Dallas, a unit of True North Communications. He had
been associate creative director at Leo Burnett Venezuela, part of
the Leo Burnett Co.
</P>
<P>
   _ Neal Vitale, president and chief operating officer at the
Petersen Cos., New York, resigned ``to pursue other business
opportunities,'' the company said, including working with some of
Petersen's major equity investors. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
